<subSubSection id="7AC9282CA07640C9346E4ACD87F948B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="AF1EBC17615AED8FC61D9863AE2ABE2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1324B574DB3BF47739DBA79FBF63496" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="7117D897CB736259DDEB7F90837313A5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male. Coloration</emphasis>
: Body blackish brown with yellowish brown lateral border (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="74938D39D4003521C666BDBC2E3143E9" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8A, B, E, F</figureCitation>
). Pronotum blackish brown with a pair of large black stripes, which are separated or contiguous near the anterior margin, lateral borders and disc yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8BB07E597276CA526A98DED4F23B6B3C" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8L</figureCitation>
); mesonotum and metanotum blackish brown with disc yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C9450AA5CDFBB6390FE4FD360F83F5B8" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8A, E</figureCitation>
). Head yellowish brown with a black patch at vertex, antenna brown with a black spot near outer margin of antennal sockets respectively or forming a T-shaped stripe on the face (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EF7DEA8B01B68AAE049A8FA7E5EE08FA" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8M</figureCitation>
). Legs yellowish brown with some irregular blackish brown stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="85990862EB29DBA1B55D23220F6199EA" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8A, E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="F95F7A87A6F7A492B6E9E9B1AC7CFF6C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Head</emphasis>
: Interocular space slightly less than ocelli width and distinctly narrower than width of antennal sockets (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="53EF859FAB6D6D79CDA0F5923DE98688" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8M</figureCitation>
). The third and fifth of maxillary palps about the same length, and slightly longer than the fourth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8704616E4F4E1BD40D64D04EF775BF01" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8I</figureCitation>
). Pronotum trapezoidal (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3CD396F212A572E825B5BD79354F7170" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8L</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="61F732C22EC1E46FCF0D61519F1C7247" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Tegmina and hindwings</emphasis>
: Both scaly and strongly reduced, only extending to about the end of mesonotum and metanotum, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="563FB2CEC982793E17EBB36A8FD0CF64" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8N, O</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="CE3F8B06A79B4795011D1E0E8C6C280C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Legs</emphasis>
: Anteroventral margin of front femur Type B3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F4E6588B6090233672296B25EF10597D" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8J</figureCitation>
), pretarsal claws symmetrical and unspecialized. 
<emphasis id="499C5F65E668F1630FE5A7A36F100C68" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Abdominal tergites</emphasis>
: Middle of T7 slightly raised with setal tuft, and a pair of inconspicuous fossae on either side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C93BAE9AA785162E8A576E7D9E91A08" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8K</figureCitation>
). T10 flat with anterior border concave and hind margin also slightly concave in the middle. 
<emphasis id="C850BD50C7B6183A3A8B678B245131A7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: Dissimilar, the right one with a strongly curved and slender process, the left one bifurcated with apices rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ACA35718627274B1D1E4BB7CF5B7A1BF" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8P</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="FC810337DC7A6EC29E95BD73F3F8AA16" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Subgenital plate</emphasis>
: Distinctly asymmetrical, the left posterior margin broadly and concavely excavated; styli nearly conical and arising from the right posterior angle, the right one slightly larger than the left one (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C58CA14893E8DC24290F2E156012466E" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8T</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="752BDB2BA236D18680468B540823F3BB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: L3 on the left side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A47E2FBA78520EA013A0F4E32DFC8BF4" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8Q</figureCitation>
); L2vm rod-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A1A6809C43C9E13FACDB38CAC50EF6E7" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8R</figureCitation>
); R2, R3 consisting of several sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D2100D55C04681E767622373558618B0" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8S</figureCitation>
). - 
<emphasis id="06C71A0C77FCFABA138D86BAE5D018B5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to the male but body larger (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="41091CBF7CB83FB3EDBF8BD686E5D64B" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Blattella foliolata sp. nov., A, B male, adult: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C, D female, adult: C paratype, dorsal view; D paratype, ventral view; E, F male, nymph: E dorsal view; F ventral view; G, H female, nymph: G dorsal view; H ventral view; I maxillary palp; J front femur, ventral view; K seventh abdominal tergite; L pronotum; M head, ventral view; N tegmen; O wing; P supra-anal plate, ventral view; Q left phallomere; R median phallomere; S right phallomere; T subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A-H), 1 mm (K-O), 0.5 mm (I, J, P-T)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690408" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">8C, D, G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
