<subSubSection id="A01A3E70E0848BCF6376DD99EC761510" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="08E3D70247F7EBEB75AA61A69C5571B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAA721C8D67A0B243CE307FFFC798B9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="C9AC0F7568FCA414D4CD2ECDF68B8E8E" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella foliolata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliolata">
<emphasis id="D6F5DCC4DA39489CE47B2F0579DFC1D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella foliolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jin and Che 
<emphasis id="2C1D06746A8117916780D5737E739C7B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="84CC10AC7A696A0CB394FDCB49629CFD" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Ignabolivaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ignabolivaria bilobata" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis id="535EB1E84F11776EC29BF84DA3CA492D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Ignabolivaria bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chopard, 1929 because of nearly identical scale-shaped tegmina and wings. However, they can be distinguished by the following: 1) the former with black markings on the face, but the latter entirely dark brown; 2) abdominal T7 longer than the previous tergites in the former, but shorter than most of previous tergites in the latter; 3) styli close to each other in the former, but separated by a distance of about the length of one stylus in the latter. Meanwhile, this species is easily recognized and distinguished from other macropterous 
<taxonomicName id="355C39F4BB871995604FE30D96122935" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="765664D1C756548DA55687A3B1D65F9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species owing to the strongly reduced wings, but it is very challenging to distinguish them from the nymphs of 
<taxonomicName id="A0F8B55DB766A61651A3CCBAF4CAC616" baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella bisignata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisignata">
<emphasis id="5167669EFC9310EE08B31713A5EB4E80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella bisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893) in the wild. Like most species of 
<taxonomicName id="8F9B22131E2CD62AA2ACBE2CBA25A3FB" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3321CEB06FEBB054431EB9D2EDD35EFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the brachypterous 
<taxonomicName id="F0A37F85773F9A0C87A105AB531562F1" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella foliolata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliolata">
<emphasis id="170873F9EB39CB693C4F6B43CE0CCB0D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella foliolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jin and Che 
<emphasis id="358191D220FF1DA0A1BF4390564585E1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">sp. nov.</emphasis>
has a small body, pronotum blackish brown with a pair of large black stripes, a symmetrical T10, and an asymmetrical subgenital plate with a concave excavation on the left posterior margin. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="8774DB0636D3ABD9B16372FA5D784C3E" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella foliolata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliolata">
<emphasis id="7D6D3A646783B2BB73971B28C70DA91E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella foliolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jin and Che 
<emphasis id="C0C084DE78CFD291B5A3C20E9805EAD5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">sp. nov.</emphasis>
was deeply embedded within the clade of 
<taxonomicName id="83521C348FF5916F8210633D04579C73" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3B5A5D605B7E0A52938B9EA059C29F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in our phylogenetic analysis, and is retrieved as the sister group of 
<taxonomicName id="DE82D75750E9B86001CBF400354F27FA" genus="B." lsidName="B. bisignata" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="bisignata">
<emphasis id="8D11A3C40B692683C2C8E173BCDF3F59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">B. bisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="CBE957BF993D4A26F1346D22BBBAB918" genus="B." lsidName="B. nipponica" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="nipponica">
<emphasis id="DC8BF71339CF5A93208468C93DC16845" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">B. nipponica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="6B4BE8CBDB929E9A8B2C36D233E309FC" genus="B." lsidName="B. germanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis id="D28236EB37BF0D10C3EB29F439BFF6E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">B. germanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="7315CFEEF41F7265DE6C0380129B29F5" genus="B." lsidName="B. parilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="parilis">
<emphasis id="01EF1180FE460AD705C0245E0983CAAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">B. parilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="78EFAA0AC4C5D496AB8EC104FEF96875" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E17B81856EB961B9C70512E2F1682C8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="812C099CEFF459A804F761D2D2BE93A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="427F19D836AE041B3EA7476C52DA6656" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
The Latin word 
<emphasis id="113478B9C6FEED0F85C37F8B41F8AB07" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">foliolatus</emphasis>
refers to the tegmina and hindwings strongly reduced as a lobule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="222FCD0A4423FCD575B8AF3F966AC424" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="86B4BBF7BC4A41E9C237AE3DB7254F7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1702E94F64464C499494AD44C743A0ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">China (Sichuan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
